    "In contrast, male scores were significantly higher in the \"software and multimedia, \" \"hardware, \" \"security, \" and \"interest-knowledge\" domains and total scores.",
    "The most apparent difference between median scores of genders was observed in the \"security\" area, where the difference was 0.50 points out of a 1-5 scale (p: 0.0288).",
    "(Table 4).Spearman correlation test showed that there were weak positive correlations between the years and the \"software and multimedia\"(p: 0.0008, rho: 0.1539), \"ethics\" (p: 0.0001, rho: 0.1830), \"interest and knowledge\" (p: 0.0041, rho: 0.1315) domains and the average score (p: 0.0230, rho: 0.1046).",
    "No significant correlation was detected between the years and the \"hardware, \" \"network, \" \"security, \" and \"A.I. \"",
    "fields (p values > 0.1865) (Supplementary Table 1)."
